description:
What is abiding in Christ? In John 15, Jesus told the disciples four times “Abide in Me.” What did Jesus mean, in practical terms? Exactly what does it mean to abide in Christ? 

In the third and final part of this series, Pastor Pavel Goia explains what it means to abide in Christ. This essential element is often lacking in our Christian life, even though we know that the only security we have is to be fully connected to Christ. We cannot experience victory or produce fruits without abiding in Christ. But how do we put it into practice? 

David was a sinner and yet he yearned to be in God’s presence. He said, “My soul longeth, yea, even fainteth for the courts of the Lord” (Psalm 84:2). To David, God’s presence was better than anything. What can we learn from David’s experience? Mary Magdalene was a sinner but she, too, longed to be near to Christ. What can her experience teach us? What is the difference between the experiences of the Bible saints and our own? Learn the key to having a thriving, growing, victorious Christian experience. Find out what it means to abide in Christ.
